2010-10-16 07:20
	* Vic Cherubini <vmc@leftnode.com> Wrote the write() method to save the form data as serialized JSON to a datastore. It's not the prettiest thing, but it's very fast and only requires one table. Additionally, added the ability to change the name of the table that the data is stored to. It is 'form' by default, but the user could easily change it to something else. (07:20:31)

